cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation using neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on digit recognition and sentiment analysis, which are tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), respectively. The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel method for training neural networks, which could be of interest to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
